         "description":"MANDATORY: You MUST describe what you see in the images (Charts, System Models) to prove you have analyzed them.",
         "value":"The paper includes several figures and tables. Figure 1 illustrates the concept of photonic-based THz ISAC for fiber-wireless networks and the principle of full-photonic THz ISAC signal generation, direct LFM reception, and de-chirping. Figure 2 shows the experimental setup of the photonic-based D-band THz ISAC system. Figure 3 presents the true-to-false target power ratio (TFTPR) of the signal from the BPD. Figure 4 displays the spectrums after FFT operation with TFLN-MZM operating at different bias points. Figure 5 shows the tested S11 and S21 parameters of the TFLN-MZM. Figure 6 presents the optical spectrums at different points in the system. Figure 7 shows the sensing SNR with different carrier frequencies and Vpp. Figure 8 presents the range resolution and sensing SNR with varying fiber lengths. Figure 9 illustrates the range profiles for the target at different distances and the measured distances before calibration. Figure 10 displays the BER with different center frequencies, Vpp, and baud rates."
      },
